===Etymology 1===
From {{etyl|enm|en}} {{m|enm|bageard||marked by a badge}}, from {{m|enm|bage||badge}}, referring to the animal's badge-like white blaze, equivalent to {{suffix|badge|ard|lang=en}}.

====Noun====
[[Image:Meles meles MHNT.jpg|thumb|A badger]]
{{en-noun}}

# A common name for any [[mammal]] of three subfamilies, which belong to the family [[Mustelidae]]: [[Melinae]] (Eurasian badgers), [[Mellivorinae]] ([[ratel]] or [[honey badger]]), and ''{{taxlink|Taxideinae|subfamily|noshow=1}}'' ([[American badger]]).
# A [[native]] or [[resident]] of the American state, [[Wisconsin]].
# {{context|obsolete|lang=en}} A brush made of badger hair.
# {{context|in the plural|obsolete|vulgar|cant|lang=en}} A crew of desperate [[villain]]s who robbed near rivers, into which they threw the bodies of those they murdered.

